```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

df = pd.read_excel("/content/bilateralmigrationmatrix20170_Apr2018 - EU.xlsx")
columns = df.columns
connections={}
for indice, fila in df.iterrows():
  targets={}
  cont = 1
  for i in range(len(fila)):
    if fila[i] != fila["Dimension"]:
      targets[columns[cont]]=fila[i]
      cont += 1
  connections[fila["Dimension"]]=targets
```


```python
chords = pd.DataFrame(columns=['source', 'target', 'value'])
nodes_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['name'])
for country, target_data in connections.items():
    print(country)
    # We want to insert into our nodes df and use that index as the numerical representation in the chords dataframe.
    if country not in nodes_df['name'].values:
        new_row={'name': country}
        nodes_df.loc[len(nodes_df)] = new_row
    country_id = int(nodes_df[nodes_df['name'] == country].index[0])


    for target, counts in target_data.items():
        if target not in nodes_df['name'].values:
            new_row={'name': target}
            nodes_df.loc[len(nodes_df)] = new_row
        target_id = int(nodes_df[nodes_df['name'] == target].index[0])

        # During our process in the last code block, we add each count twice:
        # Once for the source and once for the target. So, we want to make sure we add it only once.
        is_already_in = chords[(chords['source'] == target_id) & (chords['target'] == country_id)]
        if len(is_already_in) == 0:
            new_row = {'source': country_id, 'target': target_id, 'value': counts}
            chords.loc[len(chords)] = new_row

# Make sure our values are ints.
chords['value'] = chords['value'].astype('int')
```
